Text.text: Eclipse Steady analyses the impact of vulnerabilities in open-source software in specific application contexts.
The following three assessment levels represent an increasing security risk for the application under analysis, and are displayed in the 'Vulnerabilities' tab:
(1) an application depends on a version of a OSS archive with known vulnerabilities
(2) an application can potentially execute vulnerable code of a vulnerable archive version
(3) an application actually executes vulnerable code
This assessment is done by joining information stemming from NVD, OSS repositories, application tests and static source code analysis.
Henrik Plate, Serena Ponta, Antonino Sabetta (SAP Security Research)
